    "privileged_info_summary": "This is a synthetic hiking resupply task based on a 21-day Pacific Crest Trail section (Section J) starting June 15, 2024. The trail dataset contains 21 days of precomputed daily mileages ranging from 9.8 to 18.2 miles, totaling 288.8 miles. Resupply points are located at days 5 (Kennedy Meadows), 11 (Grumpy Bear), 16 (Trail Pass), and 21 (Rock Creek). The task is graded on cumulative distance calculations, food weight calculations (2 lbs per day), pace validation against terrain difficulty limits (Easy ≤20, Moderate ≤15, Hard ≤12, Very Hard ≤8 mi/day), and sequential date calculations. A critical data issue exists: the verifier expects total distance of 180-280 miles, but the trail data generates 288.8 miles, exceeding this range. Additionally, three days of the trail have unrealistic paces exceeding their terrain difficulty limits.",
